{"parse":{"title":"Spectra (installation)","pageid":43484616,"revid":849479894,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:172px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_above_chimney_tops.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d5/Spectra_above_chimney_tops.png/170px-Spectra_above_chimney_tops.png\" width=\"170\" height=\"272\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d5/Spectra_above_chimney_tops.png/255px-Spectra_above_chimney_tops.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/d5/Spectra_above_chimney_tops.png/340px-Spectra_above_chimney_tops.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"2207\" data-file-height=\"3532\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_above_chimney_tops.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><i>spectra [london]</i>, 2014. The beam could be seen for miles above the rooftops and chimneys of London.</div></div></div>\n<p><i><b>Spectra</b></i> is the name of a series of art <a href=\"/wiki/Installation_art\" title=\"Installation art\">installations</a> by <a href=\"/wiki/Ryoji_Ikeda\" title=\"Ryoji Ikeda\">Ryoji Ikeda</a> which use intense white light as a sculptural material.<sup id=\"cite_ref-RI_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RI-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The most recent presentation of <i>spectra</i> was in Hobart, Tasmania, Australia for four days ending 24 June, 2018 to mark the winter solstice, and as an installation piece at the <a href=\"/wiki/MONA_FOMA\" title=\"MONA FOMA\">Dark Mofo</a> festival held by <a href=\"/wiki/Museum_of_Old_and_New_Art\" title=\"Museum of Old and New Art\">MONA</a>. <i>spectra [Amsterdam]</i> was the first presentation of the work in 2008 its current form; an array of xenon lamps pointed skywards lit from dusk till dawn accompanied by a mathematically derived score audible from each of the lamp bases. The work was first commissioned and produced by Forma Arts.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#spectra_[tasmania],_2013_&amp;_2018\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>spectra [tasmania]</i>, 2013 &amp; 2018</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#spectra_[london],_2014\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>spectra [london]</i>, 2014</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Gallery\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Gallery</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Spectra_(installation)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Ryoji Ikeda has produced <i>spectra</i> installations in a number of locations, all in several different configurations. The first was a tunnel of light and sound at <a href=\"/wiki/John_F._Kennedy_International_Airport\" title=\"John F. Kennedy International Airport\">JFK Airport</a> at Eero Saarinen's abandoned TWA Terminal in New York in 2004.<sup id=\"cite_ref-RI_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RI-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  Four site-specific light and sound installations were created across <a href=\"/wiki/Amsterdam\" title=\"Amsterdam\">Amsterdam</a> in 2008 for the city's <i>Dream Amsterdam</i> event.<sup id=\"cite_ref-RI_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RI-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  A more concentrated 64-beam installation was then created in Paris that year for their annual <i><a href=\"/wiki/Nuit_Blanche\" title=\"Nuit Blanche\">Nuit Blanche</a></i> festival.<sup id=\"cite_ref-RI_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RI-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  Other cities which have hosted the installation include <a href=\"/wiki/Buenos_Aires\" title=\"Buenos Aires\">Buenos Aires</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Hobart\" title=\"Hobart\">Hobart</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-HobartABC_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HobartABC-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/wiki/Nagoya\" title=\"Nagoya\">Nagoya</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-RI_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RI-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"spectra_.5Btasmania.5D.2C_2013_.26_2018\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"spectra_[tasmania],_2013_&amp;_2018\"><i>spectra [tasmania]</i>, 2013 &amp; 2018</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Spectra_(installation)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: spectra [tasmania], 2013 &amp; 2018\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_%26_Full_Moon_from_Mt_Wellington_(9111132653).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Spectra_%26_Full_Moon_from_Mt_Wellington_%289111132653%29.jpg/220px-Spectra_%26_Full_Moon_from_Mt_Wellington_%289111132653%29.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Spectra_%26_Full_Moon_from_Mt_Wellington_%289111132653%29.jpg/330px-Spectra_%26_Full_Moon_from_Mt_Wellington_%289111132653%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Spectra_%26_Full_Moon_from_Mt_Wellington_%289111132653%29.jpg/440px-Spectra_%26_Full_Moon_from_Mt_Wellington_%289111132653%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4272\" data-file-height=\"2848\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_%26_Full_Moon_from_Mt_Wellington_(9111132653).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><i>spectra [tasmania]</i> pierces the <a href=\"/wiki/Hobart\" title=\"Hobart\">Hobart</a> Skyline, 22 June 2013.</div></div></div>\n<p><i>spectra [tasmania]</i> was an installation of 49 Xenon searchlights. It was placed in front of <a href=\"/wiki/Hobart_Cenotaph\" title=\"Hobart Cenotaph\">Hobart's Cenotaph</a> on the western shore of that city's central business district. Installed and active from sunset to sunrise 14 - 23 June 2013 as part of The Red Queen, a group exhibition for 1st Dark Mofo Festival. It was estimated to reach 5-15km into the sky, depending on the weather.<sup id=\"cite_ref-HobartABC_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-HobartABC-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> In 2018 it was displayed from the grounds of MONA (Museum of Old and New Art) with the addition of Ikeda's accompanying soundscape, where it was confirmed that plans were in place to house <i>spectra</i> at the museum permanently.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"spectra_.5Blondon.5D.2C_2014\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"spectra_[london],_2014\"><i>spectra [london]</i>, 2014</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Spectra_(installation)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: spectra [london], 2014\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_London.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Spectra_London.jpg/220px-Spectra_London.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"331\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Spectra_London.jpg/330px-Spectra_London.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Spectra_London.jpg/440px-Spectra_London.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3280\" data-file-height=\"4928\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_London.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Spectra London, Victoria Tower Gardens</div></div></div>\n<p>The London installation consisted similarly of 49 Xenon searchlights shining together into the sky, accompanied by a <a href=\"/wiki/Soundscape\" title=\"Soundscape\">soundscape</a>. This presentation of <i>Spectra</i> was produced and presented by <a href=\"/wiki/Artangel\" title=\"Artangel\">Artangel</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and co-commissioned by <a href=\"/wiki/Mayor_of_London\" title=\"Mayor of London\">Mayor of London</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Boris_Johnson\" title=\"Boris Johnson\">Boris Johnson</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/14-18_NOW\" title=\"14-18 NOW\">14-18 NOW</a> programme of the <a href=\"/wiki/Imperial_War_Museum\" title=\"Imperial War Museum\">Imperial War Museum</a> for the <a href=\"/wiki/First_World_War_centenary\" title=\"First World War centenary\">centenary of World War One</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DT_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DT-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-G_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-G-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and funded by the <a href=\"/wiki/Heritage_Lottery_Fund\" title=\"Heritage Lottery Fund\">Heritage Lottery Fund</a>. It was switched on at the end of the Lights Out event on 4 August 2014, when the lights of many buildings in the UK were turned off in recollection of <a href=\"/wiki/Edward_Grey,_1st_Viscount_Grey_of_Fallodon\" title=\"Edward Grey, 1st Viscount Grey of Fallodon\">Sir Edward Grey</a>'s famous prophecy that, \"<a href=\"/wiki/The_lamps_are_going_out\" title=\"The lamps are going out\">The lamps are going out all over Europe;</a> we shall not see them lit again in our lifetime.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-BBC_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BBC-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>  The installation was turned off for good at dawn on 11 August 2014, as the presentation was only planned to last for one week.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DT_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DT-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The spotlights used were <a href=\"/wiki/Xenon_arc_lamp\" title=\"Xenon arc lamp\">xenon arc lamps</a> requiring 4 kilowatts of power each.<sup id=\"cite_ref-G_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-G-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>  The array and the sound system was powered by four <a href=\"/wiki/Diesel_generator\" title=\"Diesel generator\">diesel generators</a> fuelled by <a href=\"/wiki/Biodiesel\" title=\"Biodiesel\">vegetable oil</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-G_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-G-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>  A crew of thirty technicians assembled, tested and maintained the installation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-G_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-G-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>  The soundscape was inspired by mathematical concepts and consisted of pure <a href=\"/wiki/Sine_wave\" title=\"Sine wave\">sine waves</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1418N_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1418N-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Gallery\">Gallery</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Spectra_(installation)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Gallery\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-packed\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 136.66666666667px\"><div style=\"width: 136.66666666667px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 134.66666666667px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Crowds_come_to_Spectra.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3d/Crowds_come_to_Spectra.jpg/202px-Crowds_come_to_Spectra.jpg\" width=\"135\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3d/Crowds_come_to_Spectra.jpg/304px-Crowds_come_to_Spectra.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/3d/Crowds_come_to_Spectra.jpg/405px-Crowds_come_to_Spectra.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2769\" data-file-height=\"2463\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Crowds are drawn to the nightly spectacle in London\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 180.66666666667px\"><div style=\"width: 180.66666666667px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 178.66666666667px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_close-up.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/84/Spectra_close-up.jpg/268px-Spectra_close-up.jpg\" width=\"179\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/84/Spectra_close-up.jpg/402px-Spectra_close-up.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/84/Spectra_close-up.jpg/536px-Spectra_close-up.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3069\" data-file-height=\"2062\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Spectators can get in amongst the lights in London\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 128px\"><div style=\"width: 128px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 126px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_by_the_Victoria_Tower.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4c/Spectra_by_the_Victoria_Tower.jpg/189px-Spectra_by_the_Victoria_Tower.jpg\" width=\"126\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4c/Spectra_by_the_Victoria_Tower.jpg/283px-Spectra_by_the_Victoria_Tower.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4c/Spectra_by_the_Victoria_Tower.jpg/378px-Spectra_by_the_Victoria_Tower.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2869\" data-file-height=\"2736\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>The base of the London installation was in <a href=\"/wiki/Victoria_Tower_Gardens\" title=\"Victoria Tower Gardens\">Victoria Tower Gardens</a>\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 182.66666666667px\"><div style=\"width: 182.66666666667px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 180.66666666667px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_London_2.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Spectra_London_2.jpg/271px-Spectra_London_2.jpg\" width=\"181\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Spectra_London_2.jpg/406px-Spectra_London_2.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Spectra_London_2.jpg/541px-Spectra_London_2.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4928\" data-file-height=\"3280\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Spectra London\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 182.66666666667px\"><div style=\"width: 182.66666666667px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 180.66666666667px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_London_3.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/84/Spectra_London_3.jpg/271px-Spectra_London_3.jpg\" width=\"181\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/84/Spectra_London_3.jpg/406px-Spectra_London_3.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/84/Spectra_London_3.jpg/541px-Spectra_London_3.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4928\" data-file-height=\"3280\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Looking up towards the sky while standing in the middle of Spectra London\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 182.66666666667px\"><div style=\"width: 182.66666666667px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 180.66666666667px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_London_4.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/df/Spectra_London_4.jpg/271px-Spectra_London_4.jpg\" width=\"181\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/df/Spectra_London_4.jpg/406px-Spectra_London_4.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/df/Spectra_London_4.jpg/541px-Spectra_London_4.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4342\" data-file-height=\"2890\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Spectra London\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 182.66666666667px\"><div style=\"width: 182.66666666667px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 180.66666666667px;\"><div style=\"margin:0px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Spectra_London_5.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Spectra_London_5.jpg/271px-Spectra_London_5.jpg\" width=\"181\" height=\"120\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Spectra_London_5.jpg/406px-Spectra_London_5.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Spectra_London_5.jpg/541px-Spectra_London_5.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"4928\" data-file-height=\"3280\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Spectra London\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Spectra_(installation)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Cathedral_of_light\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Cathedral of light\">Cathedral of light</a>, a 1937 Nazi propaganda display with massed searchlights pointing skyward</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Luxor_Hotel#Beam\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Luxor Hotel\">Luxor Hotel and Casino skybeam</a>, currently the world's brightest searchlight display</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/A_Symphony_of_Lights\" title=\"A Symphony of Lights\">A Symphony of Lights</a>, a light display across Hong Kong harbour</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Tribute_in_Light\" title=\"Tribute in Light\">Tribute in Light</a>, a memorial of the 11 September attack on the World Trade Centre</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Spectra_(installation)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-RI-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-RI_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-RI_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-RI_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-RI_1-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a